[1] USA (New Jersey)
Date: Fri 17 Oct 2014
Source: MyCentralJersey [summ., edited]
http://www.mycentraljersey.com/story/news/local/somerset-county/2014/10/17/bound-brook-high-reports-enterovirus-case/17434327/


A case of enterovirus EV-D68 has been confirmed at Bound Brook High School [Somerset County, New Jersey], Superintendent of Schools Daniel Gallagher wrote in a recent posting on the school district's website. The school district's administration and physician worked with the district's physician and the Middle-Brook Regional Health Department to ensure that all of the proper protocols were being followed, Gallagher said. Those protocols included a "thorough cleaning of the building" to ensure that it is safe for students and staff members, Gallagher said.

Enteroviruses (EV) are common viruses with more than 100 different types that are around mostly in the summer and fall. EV infections can cause mild or severe symptoms, and are more common in infants, children and teenagers. The state has confirmed 17 cases of EV-D68 in New Jersey.

For more information, visit http://www.nj.gov/health/cd/ev-d60/index.shtml.

